<p>WELCOME TO 'ANKN MORPORK'!!!!</p>
<p>Here you can find lots of interesting people and a lot of dangerous.....</p>
<p>You should earn enough money in order to buy a ticket from this city</p>
<p>But until you, my friend, did't do it, be careful, good luck to you!!!</p>
<p>During the game you will meet members of different 
    guildsEach of them has its own rules and rewards for their services</p>
<p>Initially, your money account is 100 Ankh-Morpork dollars
    You should have 200 Ankh-Morpork dollars in order to leave this city</p>

<p>You can meet :</p>
<br />
<p>
    <h3>-Assasins' guild</h3> <br />
    Is a school for professional killers,this guild takes payment in the range of 5 to 30 
    but each assasin has their own payment range
</p>
<br />
<p>
    <h3>-Beggars' Guild</h3> <br />
    Is the oldest, largest and (perhaps surprisingly) richest of the city's many guilds.
    It has a very strict code of practice and enforced hierarchy each beggar has its own payment
</p>
<br />
<p>
    <h3>-Guild of Thieves</h3> <br />
    Being completely legal Guild of Thieves is responsible for ensuring a socially acceptable number of thefts.
    Player can get robbed anytime and will have to pay a standard fee in amount 10 AM$ to the guild member.
    But total number of thefts during the game can’t be greater then socially acceptable number of thefts.
</p>
<br />
<p>
    <h3>-Clown guild</h3> <br />
    Walking the city you may meet one of a very good friends,
    they won't kill you and give you a chance to earn some money
</p>
